nds by a factor of up to 1,000 and\neffectively reduces the energy threshold of our simulated TPC by $30\\%$ for\nfluorine recoils and $50\\%$ for helium recoils. We also find that the 3DCNN\nreduces electron backgrounds by up to a factor of 20 compared to the shallow\nmachine learning approaches, corresponding to a 2 $\\rm keV_{ee}$ reduction in\nthe energy threshold.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Jun 2022 03:34:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-23"}
